<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n37009o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n37" href="#n37009o">N37 (VI.B.28A)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n37all.htm#n37009o"> 9(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 254 Tom Thumb &frasl; Two Dromios <small>Black</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n37009o"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<font size="-1">THE DWARF&apos;S DUEL, OR THE MARRIAGE OF THE MIDGETS</font>]</font>: In December, 1861, a dwarf <font color="green">[George Washington Morrison Nutt]</font> visited Barnum at the Museum, who promised to be a great success with the public. <font color="green">[And whose services B. later purchased for 30,000 dollars.]</font> &hellip; Barnum rechristened his new dwarf Commodore Nutt, after the manner of General <mark>Tom Thumb</mark>, and he was dressed in naval uniform. &hellip; In August, 1862, the rivals <font color="green">[long believed by the public to be one and the same dwarf]</font>, advertised as &ldquo;<mark>The Two Dromios</mark>&rdquo;, appeared toigether. <small> M.R. Werner, <a name="MRWP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MRWP"><cite title="source">P.T. Barnum</cite></a> (1923) 254</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
